Study: Presymptomatic Transmission of SARS-CoV-2 — Singapore, January 23–March 16, 2020
Journal: CDC: Morbidity and Mortality Weekly Report
Excerpt: Among the 243 cases of COVID-19 reported in Singapore as of March 16, 157 were locally acquired; 10 of the 157 (6.4%) locally acquired cases are included in these clusters and were attributed to presymptomatic transmission.
